    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-31T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-31T06:00:00-05:00" n="908"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d908">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/764: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-31T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 31, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 1—5:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1096. My 1008, October 11. Embassy forwarded with the courier who left Ankara
                    last night the 4 bomb sights and other secret <pb facs="0814" n="802"
                        xml:id="pg_802"/> instruments which were part of equipment of the 4 United
                    States Army bombers interned in Turkey. The courier is accompanied by the
                    Assistant Military Attaché Captain Brown who will look after the security of
                    instruments until their delivery to appropriate authorities in Lydda.</p>
                <p>Please inform Ambassador Steinhardt.<note n="99" xml:id="d908fn99">Temporarily in
                        the United States.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kelley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
